Explanation of results:

- I inspected app/Http/Controllers/PostCommentController.php. The index method returns a view('comments.index', [...]) where 'comments' is a collection from $post->comments()->with('author')->latest()->get(). This indicates the endpoint renders an HTML view (server-side rendered) containing the comments for the given post.
- The route for this controller is registered as a web resource route in routes/web.php: Route::resource('posts.comments', PostCommentController::class)->only('index'); so this is a web (HTML) endpoint, not an API JSON endpoint.
- Laravel route-model binding is used (Post $post). If the post cannot be resolved, Laravel will return a 404 response (Not Found). Therefore a 404 response should be documented.
- The successful response is HTML (rendered view). In Swagger 2.0 Response Objects, I represent the body as a string with format "html".
- I include two response status codes: 200 (successful HTML view) and 404 (post not found, typically an HTML error page). I did not include references ($ref) or other fields beyond standard Response Object properties (description and schema), as requested.

